            <text>No special characters breaking XML parsing?</text>
            <option id="A">Yes</option><option id="B">No</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Clean text check.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>All options A, B, C, D present?</text>
            <option id="A">Yes</option><option id="B">No</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Structural check.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Explanations provided for all questions?</text>
            <option id="A">Yes</option><option id="B">No</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Content check.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Physics Batch 1 (4 chapters) finished.</text>
            <option id="A">Yes</option><option id="B">No</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Milestone reached.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Relative permeability of air is approx ____.</text>
            <option id="A">1</option><option id="B">0</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>χ is negligible.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Magnetic needle at the poles remains in ____ direction.</text>
            <option id="A">Any horizontal (stable in vertical)</option><option id="B">North-South</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Bh is zero, so no horizontal restoring force.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>The magnetic field of Earth is due to ____ in the core.</text>
            <option id="A">Convection currents (Dynamo Effect)</option><option id="B">Permanent magnets</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Currents in liquid outer core.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Does the magnetic field of Earth change with time?</text>
            <option id="A">Yes (Secular variations)</option><option id="B">No</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Slow changes in intensity and direction.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Reverse magnetization cycle loss is called ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Hysteresis</option><option id="B">Eddy current</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Leading to energy dissipate as heat.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Is water diamagnetic or paramagnetic?</text>
            <option id="A">Diamagnetic</option><option id="B">Paramagnetic</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Paired electrons in H2O molecule.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Susceptibility χ of superconductor is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">-1</option><option id="B">0</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>χ = μ_r - 1 = 0 - 1 = -1.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Bohr Magneton value in J/T is approx ____.</text>
            <option id="A">9.27 x 10^-24</option><option id="B">1.6 x 10^-19</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>m = IA unit J/T is same as A.m^2.</explanation></question>
